/*
HAGIWO MOD2 01 Metal Hit RP2350 Ver1.0

  - One-shot sound source with inharmonic overtones, like striking metal
  - Three potentiometers control Ring Decay / Metal Spread / Strike Tune
  - A rising edge on trigger input GPIO7 plays one sound
  - BUTTON GPIO6 works as an alternate switch. Each press toggles the PUSH / SW state
  - While PUSH / SW is ON, Strike Tune is raised by 2 octaves
  - The PUSH / SW state is saved to pseudo EEPROM and restored on reboot
  - Accent input GPIO0 is checked at trigger time. If HIGH, that note plays at 50% volume
  - LED GPIO5 lights for 20 msec on trigger
  - ADC and PUSH state are latched at note start. Changes during playback apply from the next note
  - A2 for Strike Tune prioritizes input response and is read once 5 msec after the trigger rising edge
  - The waiting audio buffer is rebuilt immediately after trigger to reduce pitch response delay
  - A0 / A1 are not inverted. Only A2 is inverted by the circuit and corrected in firmware
  - Audio PWM output is 10-bit, PWM update rate is 96 kHz, audio generation rate is 48 kHz
  - Audio processing is kept lightweight using sine LUT, incremental envelopes, and simple soft clipping
  - ADC DMA input + PWM DMA output + dual-core processing

  --Pin assign---
POT1     A0       Ring Decay, 40 ms to 1200 ms, non-inverted
POT2     A1       Metal Spread, ADC1<=100 uses harmonic ratios, 101 and above uses conventional inharmonic ratios, non-inverted
POT3     A2       Strike Tune, 40 Hz base, 1V/oct, inverted ADC corrected in firmware
IN1      GPIO7    Trigger input, rising edge plays one sound
IN2      GPIO0    Accent input, if HIGH at trigger time that note plays at 50% volume
CV       A2       Shared with POT3
OUT      GPIO1    Audio PWM output, 10-bit
BUTTON   GPIO6    PUSH / SW input, internal pullup, toggles ON/OFF on each press, raises Strike Tune by +2 octaves while ON
LED      GPIO5    Lights for 20 msec on trigger
EEPROM   Flash    Saves PUSH / SW state. Commits only once, 100 msec or later after button press


